I would suggest *not* to postprocess this with Javascript - but already do this on the `query` side:

https://www.db-fiddle.com/f/9edg4MvKxJ7BUmHhhuAPjE/0

```
CREATE TYPE email AS (
  email text,
  verified boolean
);

CREATE TABLE emails (
  email email
);

INSERT INTO emails (email) VALUES (ROW(&#39;test@abc.com&#39;, false));
```

```
SELECT 
jsonb_build_object(&#39;email&#39;, (email).email, &#39;verified&#39;, (email).verified) as email
FROM emails;

-- {&quot;email&quot;:&quot;test@abc.com&quot;,&quot;verified&quot;:false}

```

This way it should be more performant/faster and side affects free from client code.

